-- Monte Paschi stocks fail to open on expectations of bigger cap hike
-- By Lisa Jucca
-- Tue Apr 15, 2014 03:10AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, April 15 (Reuters) - Shares in Banca Monte dei Paschi di Siena <BMPS.MI>, Italy's third-largest bank by assets, failed to open on Tuesday after reports the management is considering increasing the size of a planned capital increase to up to 5 billion euros ($6.91 billion).

